C#

(ref and out keyword)
(ref) - Passing the variable by reference, not by the value
        Intialise the value before passing it
        
  (E.g program)
    public class Program{
      static void main(string args[]){
          int number = 10;
          Console.WriteLine("First" + number);
          ChangeNumber(ref number);
          Console.WriteLine("Second" + number);
        }
      public void ChangeNumber(int ref value){
          value = 69;
      }
    }
